<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="232" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1871,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1871,1897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to the memory of famous Japanese manga cartoonist – Kentaro Miura.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="234" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1871,2042]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="233" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1943,1969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
In a key to species of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, T. &amp; Kon, M. &amp; Kakizoe, S." box="[695,890,1943,1969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref8804" refString="Ochi, T., Kon, M. &amp; Kakizoe, S. (2016) Nine new taxa of the genus Gilletianus from Southeast Asia (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 22 (2), 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="2016">
Ochi 
<emphasis box="[754,808,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Minkina" authorityName="Minkina" authorityYear="2022" box="[899,1108,1943,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miurai" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[899,1006,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">G. miurai</emphasis>
Minkina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1117,1249,1943,1969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara, 2014" authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[182,743,1979,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[182,391,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">G. sundainsulanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, T. &amp; Kon, M. &amp; Kawahara, M." box="[399,743,1979,2005]" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" pagination="635 - 648" refId="ref8893" refString="Ochi, T., Kon, M. &amp; Kawahara, M. (2014) Four new species of Aphodiini from Southeast Asia (Coleoptera Scarabaeidae). Giornale Italiano di Entomologia, 13 (59), 635 - 648." type="journal article" year="2014">Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However aedeagi of both species are distinctly different – in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[151,361,2015,2041]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[151,361,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="232">G. sundainsulanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the aedeagus is shorter, length about 2.5 mm and the parameres are relatively much shorter in relation to phallobase (about 0.39 x its length), their apices are less sharply upturned and the oblique truncature is less marked. 
<taxonomicName authority="Minkina" authorityName="Minkina" authorityYear="2022" box="[298,609,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miurai" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[298,504,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">Gilletianus miurai</emphasis>
Minkina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[620,836,187,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" rank="genus">
new species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[809,836,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[809,836,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis box="[843,1017,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">sundainsulanus</emphasis>
are in my opinion almost identical in external view. The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Minkina" authorityName="Minkina" authorityYear="2022" box="[453,665,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miurai" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[453,561,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. miurai</emphasis>
Minkina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[675,809,223,249]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the basal margin of pronotum near the middle rather more distinctly sinuate, somewhat different hind angles of pronotum and weakly sinuate clypeus anteriorly (when clypeus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[274,482,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[274,482,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. sundainsulanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather trapezoidal) but in my opinion these are very subjective differences and will probably be lost in larger series of specimens.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810130" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6810130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810130/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" startId="10.[151,264,1697,1721]" targetBox="[166,1423,394,1657]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1697,1757]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1697,1721]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">FIGURES 24–26.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara, 2014" authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[345,934,1697,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[345,622,1697,1721]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">Gilletianus sundainsulanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, T. &amp; Kon, M. &amp; Kawahara, M." box="[628,934,1697,1721]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" pagination="635 - 648" refId="ref8893" refString="Ochi, T., Kon, M. &amp; Kawahara, M. (2014) Four new species of Aphodiini from Southeast Asia (Coleoptera Scarabaeidae). Giornale Italiano di Entomologia, 13 (59), 635 - 648." type="journal article" year="2014">Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 24, habitus, male, dorsal view; 25, habitus, male, ventral view; 26, habitus, male, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1803,2010]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicName authority="Minkina" authorityName="Minkina" authorityYear="2022" box="[199,513,1803,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miurai" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[199,407,1803,1829]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">Gilletianus miurai</emphasis>
Minkina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[525,746,1803,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" rank="genus">
new species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[718,746,1804,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[718,746,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis box="[754,928,1803,1829]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">sundainsulanus</emphasis>
are additionally closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harold, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="Harold" baseAuthorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[1324,1437,1803,1830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. reichei</emphasis>
(Harold, 1859)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, T. &amp; Kon, M. &amp; Kakizoe, S." box="[385,580,1839,1865]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref8804" refString="Ochi, T., Kon, M. &amp; Kakizoe, S. (2016) Nine new taxa of the genus Gilletianus from Southeast Asia (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 22 (2), 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="2016">
Ochi 
<emphasis box="[450,509,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Minkina" authorityName="Minkina" authorityYear="2022" box="[601,918,1839,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miurai" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[601,810,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">Gilletianus miurai</emphasis>
Minkina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[932,1069,1839,1866]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
has additionally a quite similar aedeagus to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Harold" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[296,410,1875,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[296,410,1875,1902]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but still more distinctly elongate. It is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Harold" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1173,1287,1875,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[1173,1287,1875,1902]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the same features as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2014" box="[281,491,1911,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundainsulanus">
<emphasis box="[281,491,1911,1938]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. sundainsulanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
i.e.: relatively larger body, elytra proportionaly longer, distinctly different sides of pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1803,2010]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="234" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">
Additionally the shape of aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Minkina" authorityName="Minkina" authorityYear="2022" box="[632,847,1983,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miurai" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[632,742,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. miurai</emphasis>
Minkina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[858,994,1983,2010]" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara, 2010" authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="234" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindorensis">
<emphasis box="[1141,1312,1983,2010]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="233">G. mindorensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, T. &amp; Kon, M. &amp; Kawahara, M." lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="234" pageId="10" pageNumber="233" pagination="111 - 120" refId="ref8852" refString="Ochi, T., Kon, M. &amp; Kawahara, M. (2010) Four new species of the genus Gilletianus from Southeast Asia (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae). Kogane, 11, 111 - 120." type="journal article" year="2010">Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
known only from Mindoro Island. From this species it can be very easily distinguished (males) by macrosetation of elytra present only on sides and in apical third (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ochi, Kon &amp; Kawahara" authorityYear="2010" box="[944,1114,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gilletianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindorensis">
<emphasis box="[944,1114,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">G. mindorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
macrosetation on almost the whole elytra).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,815,258,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,484,258,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">Photographed material.</emphasis>
See material for comparison.
</paragraph>
